--- !u!114 &750874510
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 750874508}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Objective:\n\tAcheive the highest high\nscore possible for every level.\n\nMechanics:\n\tMatches
    can be made by\nconnecting a line of 3 or more \nof the same item, or a square\nof
    4.\n\nHow to Play:\n \nFirst, select a difficulty.\nSecond, select a Board type.\nLast,
    select the desired level.\n\nIf there are no levels, press\nthe \"Create Level\"
    button to\nmake a new level. You can make\ninfinite levels.\n\nDifficulty:\n\tDifficulty
    is determined\nby the number of item types.\nEasy has 5, Medium has 6, and\nHard
    has 7.\n\nThere is no artificial move limit\nbut not every level is created\nequal.
    Some levels may have a\nhigher natural move limit than\nothers.\n\nBoard Type:\n\tThere
    are multiple types\nof Boards. Each Difficulty has\naccess to every Board Type.
    \n\nLevels:\n\tLevels are generated\nrandomly upon creation, making\nevery level
    unique. If you ever\nfeel a level is maxed out, just\ncreate another one and
    try to\ngo even further.\n\nScoring:\n\tEach item in a match gives\na base amount,
    if the match is\nmore than 3, a score multiplier\nis applied.\n\nMultiplier:\n\tEach
    Item gives 10 points.\n3 per match is no Multiplier.\n4-5 per match is 1.2x Multiplier.\n6-8
    per match is 1.4x Multiplier.\n9+ per match is 1.8x Multiplier.\n\nExample: \n\tA
    match of 5 would be\n5 * 10 = 50, then * 1.2 = 60 points.\n\nHints:\n\tPressing
    the lightbulb will\nquickly show you any currently\npossible move. A small arrow\nwill
    appear on the items and\nindicate the direction of the\npossible move.\n\nThe
    number of possible moves\nis also shown in the top left\nof the level as \"Total
    Moves\".\n\nPowerup:\n\tFor every 1500 points you\nearn, you gain a use of the\nItem
    Switcher. This gives you\nthe ability to switch any item \non the board to the
    type of\nanother.\n\nHow to use Item Switcher:\n\tAfter pressing its button\nSelect
    the item on the board\nyou want to switch, then select\nthe type you want to
    switch it\nto.\n\nUse the Item Switcher to get\nout of a sticky situation, or\nsave
    up to set up a big combo.\n\nSaving Data:\n\tAll Data is saved locally in \nreal
    time. \n\nFor example, High Scores are\nsaved every time they are\nincreased. "
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 70a6d98c6ce034e43b79bfaa3805fb06, type: 2}
